message:
chore: update documentation

Split off development docs from README.md to DEVELOPMENT.md.
chore: update dependencies to latest versions (#9)

chore: refactor changelog, commitlint and release script

Rewrite the scripts in python and improve the changelog script to be
able to generate changelogs for single tags. This feature is used in the
release workflow on GitHub to generate a release changelog.

fix: catch up released version with actual release

We had released 0.2.0 already, but the package numbers
were not updated. So that release never got out.
Instead of removing the tag, the package are brought
up to date with that tag.
chore: update dependencies to latest versions

chore: update dependencies

Update dependencies to the latest version. This includes an update of
`eslint-config-typescript-shareable` that makes a few import/* rules
function as intended again.

Most of the changes in this commit are related to that update. Most are
simple import changes from `.` to `./Component`. On a few occasions,
some parts were refactored out.

chore: run prettier on more files

Run on all known file types by default and add more things to the
.prettierignore files instead. This simplifies the package.json script
a bit as well.

chore: update mdx to v2

Upgrade to MDX 2. There are a few changes mainly to how the code and pre
blocks work. We are now using `remark-mdx-code-meta` to read meta from
the MDX code blocks. This required a bit of a rewrite to that handling
in docs.
